{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850164728,"sessionID":"ses_287150aa0ffeBU1xudttJrSXV1","part":{"id":"prt_d78eb0d40001qav1dF9Ltn18kf","messageID":"msg_d78eb04f7001r5b9uc70ziSTlH","sessionID":"ses_287150aa0ffeBU1xudttJrSXV1","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c565d2c6958645a5a934554a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/router  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: JWT Configuration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Add JWT config fields to `Config` struct — `JWTEnabled`, `JWTAlgorithm`, `JWTSecret`, `JWTPrivateKeyPath`, `JWTPublicKeyPath`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTAudience`, `JWTExpiration`, `JWTRefreshExpiration`, `JWTClockSkew`, `JWTAllowQueryParam`\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` JWT defaults — algorithm \"HS256\", issuer \"agentcube\", expiry \"1h\", refresh expiry \"24h\", clock skew \"30s\"\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Add JWT dependency to `go.mod` — `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Phase 2: JWT Data Structures\n19: \n20: - [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTConfig` struct with all JWT settings\n21: - [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `Claims` struct embedding `jwt.RegisteredClaims` with custom fields (Roles, TenantID, Namespace)\n22: - [ ] **2.3** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserCredentials` struct for login request\n23: - [ ] **2.4** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `LoginResponse` struct for login response\n24: - [ ] **2.5** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `TokenRefreshRequest` struct\n25: - [ ] **2.6** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserValidator` interface\n26: - [ ] **2.7** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `UserClaims` struct\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## Phase 3: JWT Errors\n31: \n32: - [ ] **3.1** Define JWT error variables — `ErrMalformedToken`, `ErrInvalidSignature`, `ErrTokenExpired`, `ErrInvalidAudience`, `ErrInvalidIssuer`, `ErrUnauthorized`, `ErrInvalidCredentials`, `ErrInvalidRefreshToken`\n33: - [ ] **3.2** Define JWT error code constants\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Phase 4: JWT Manager - Core\n38: \n39: - [ ] **4.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTManager` struct with config, keys, metrics, userValidator\n40: - [ ] **4.2** Implement `NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig, validator UserValidator)` — initialize manager and load keys\n41: - [ ] **4.3** Implement key loading for HS256 (symmetric key from config/env)\n42: - [ ] **4.4** Implement key loading for RS256 (load private/public keys from files)\n43: - [ ] **4.5** Write unit test: HS256 key loading from config\n44: - [ ] **4.6** Write unit test: RS256 key loading from files\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## Phase 5: JWT Token Validation\n49: \n50: - [ ] **5.1** Implement `JWTManager.ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*Claims, error)` — parse and validate JWT\n51: - [ ] **5.2** Implement HS256 token validation with secret key\n52: - [ ] **5.3** Implement RS256 token validation with public key\n53: - [ ] **5.4** Handle signature validation errors\n54: - [ ] **5.5** Handle expiration validation with clock skew\n55: - [ ] **5.6** Handle issuer validation\n56: - [ ] **5.7** Handle audience validation\n57: - [ ] **5.8** Write unit test: Validate valid HS256 token\n58: - [ ] **5.9** Write unit test: Validate expired token returns error\n59: - [ ] **5.10** Write unit test: Validate invalid signature returns error\n60: - [ ] **5.11** Write unit test: Validate malformed token returns error\n61: - [ ] **5.12** Write unit test: Validate wrong audience returns error\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Phase 6: JWT Token Issuance\n66: \n67: - [ ] **6.1** Implement `JWTManager.IssueToken(user *UserClaims) (string, error)` — issue access token\n68: - [ ] **6.2** Implement `JWTManager.IssueRefreshToken(user *UserClaims) (string, error)` — issue refresh token\n69: - [ ] **6.3** Implement HS256 token signing\n70: - [ ] **6.4** Implement RS256 token signing\n71: - [ ] **6.5** Set claims: sub, exp, iat, nbf, iss, roles, tenant_id, namespace\n72: - [ ] **6.6** Write unit test: Issue token with correct claims\n73: - [ ] **6.7** Write unit test: Issue token with configured expiry\n74: - [ ] **6.8** Write unit test: Issue token with configured issuer\n75: - [ ] **6.9** Write unit test: RS256 token issuance\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## Phase 7: JWT Middleware\n80: \n81: - [ ] **7.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_middleware.go` — `JWTMiddleware` function\n82: - [ ] **7.2** Implement token extraction from Authorization header (Bearer token)\n83: - [ ] **7.3** Implement token extraction from query parameter (when AllowQueryParam is true)\n84: - [ ] **7.4** Implement public path check — skip JWT validation for public endpoints\n85: - [ ] **7.5** Integrate JWT validation into middleware chain\n86: - [ ] **7.6** Store claims in request context\n87: - [ ] **7.7** Store username in request context\n88: - [ ] **7.8** Write unit test: Extract token from Authorization header\n89: - [ ] **7.9** Write unit test: Extract token from query parameter\n90: - [ ] **7.10** Write unit test: Public endpoint bypasses JWT validation\n91: - [ ] **7.11** Write unit test: Protected endpoint rejects missing token\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Phase 8: Login Handler\n96: \n97: - [ ] **8.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_handler.go` — `HandleLogin` function\n98: - [ ] **8.2** Decode and validate UserCredentials from request body\n99: - [ ] **8.3** Call userValidator.Validate() with username/password\n100: - [ ] **8.4** Issue access token and refresh token on success\n101: - [ ] **8.5** Return LoginResponse with token, type, expires_in\n102: - [ ] **8.6** Return 401 on invalid credentials\n103: - [ ] **8.7** Register `/login` endpoint in router\n104: - [ ] **8.8** Write unit test: Login with valid credentials returns token\n105: - [ ] **8.9** Write unit test: Login with invalid credentials returns 401\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ## Phase 9: Refresh Handler\n110: \n111: - [ ] **9.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_handler.go` — `HandleRefresh` function\n112: - [ ] **9.2** Decode TokenRefreshRequest from request body\n113: - [ ] **9.3** Validate refresh token\n114: - [ ] **9.4** Issue new access token\n115: - [ ] **9.5** Return new access token with expires_in\n116: - [ ] **9.6** Return 401 on invalid/expired refresh token\n117: - [ ] **9.7** Register `/refresh` endpoint in router\n118: - [ ] **9.8** Write unit test: Refresh with valid token returns new access token\n119: - [ ] **9.9** Write unit test: Refresh with expired token returns 401\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## Phase 10: Router Integration\n124: \n125: - [ ] **10.1** Update router initialization to create JWTManager when JWTEnabled\n126: - [ ] **10.2** Add JWT middleware to handler chain\n127: - [ ] **10.3** Configure public paths list: `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/metrics`, `/login`, `/refresh`\n128: - [ ] **10.4** Add login and refresh endpoints to router\n129: - [ ] **10.5** Write unit test: Router with JWT enabled applies middleware\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## Phase 11: JWT Metrics\n134: \n135: - [ ] **11.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt_metrics.go` — `JWTMetrics` struct\n136: - [ ] **11.2** Implement `jwt_validated_total` counter with result label\n137: - [ ] **11.3** Implement `jwt_issued_total` counter\n138: - [ ] **11.4** Implement `jwt_refreshed_total` counter with result label\n139: - [ ] **11.5** Implement `jwt_validation_errors_total` counter with error_type label\n140: - [ ] **11.6** Integrate metrics into JWTManager\n141: - [ ] **11.7** Increment metrics on validation success/failure\n142: - [ ] **11.8** Increment metrics on token issuance\n143: - [ ] **11.9** Increment metrics on token refresh\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Phase 12: Validation\n148: \n149: - [ ] **12.1** `go build ./pkg/router/...` — successful compilation\n150: - [ ] **12.2** `go test ./pkg/router/... -v` — all unit tests pass\n151: - [ ] **12.3** Test: JWT with default config uses HS256, 1h expiry\n152: - [ ] **12.4** Test: JWT with custom config uses RS256, 24h expiry\n153: - [ ] **12.5** Test: Valid JWT token validates successfully\n154: - [ ] **12.6** Test: Expired JWT token returns 401\n155: - [ ] **12.7** Test: Invalid signature returns 401\n156: - [ ] **12.8** Test: Malformed token returns 400\n157: - [ ] **12.9** Test: Claims extracted and available in context\n158: - [ ] **12.10** Test: Login endpoint issues JWT token\n159: - [ ] **12.11** Test: Token refresh endpoint works\n160: - [ ] **12.12** Test: Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n161: - [ ] **12.13** Test: JWT metrics are exported\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Dependencies\n166: \n167: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` — JWT token handling\n168: - `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` — Metrics\n169: - AR-010 (completed) — Router Session Management\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## References\n174: \n175: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n176: - Design: `pkg/router/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: JWT Configuration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Add JWT config fields to `Config` struct — `JWTEnabled`, `JWTAlgorithm`, `JWTSecret`, `JWTPrivateKeyPath`, `JWTPublicKeyPath`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTAudience`, `JWTExpiration`, `JWTRefreshExpiration`, `JWTClockSkew`, `JWTAllowQueryParam`\n- [ ] **1.2** Implement `DefaultConfig()` JWT defaults — algorithm \"HS256\", issuer \"agentcube\", expiry \"1h\", refresh expiry \"24h\", clock skew \"30s\"\n- [ ] **1.3** Add JWT dependency to `go.mod` — `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: JWT Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/router/jwt.go` — `JWTConfig` struct with all JWT settings","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775850164706,"end":1775850164725}}}}
